                            <comment id="208787" author="sharmaso" created="Tue, 19 Sep 2017 18:33:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Olaf,&lt;br/&gt;
Do you have nodes with mlx5 cards talking to nodes with mlx4 cards in your setup?&lt;br/&gt;
 The dump cqe error is seen on the nodes with mlx5 cards. You would need &lt;del&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8752&quot; title=&quot;mlx5_warn:mlx5_0:dump_cqe:257:&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-8752&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-8752&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/del&gt; patch on the nodes with mlx5 cards. Can you check if &lt;del&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8752&quot; title=&quot;mlx5_warn:mlx5_0:dump_cqe:257:&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-8752&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-8752&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/del&gt; is included on these nodes?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="208767" author="pjones" created="Tue, 19 Sep 2017 17:17:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sonia&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Can you please advise&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Peter&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
